social_posts.post_text: Today is #LatinaEqualPayDay ! Latinas are paid just 54 cents for every $1 a white man is paid. The pay gap, harms Latinas, our families, are futures, and our entire country. Latinas must be paid fully and fairly NOW. Join us, and take action at https://justice4women.org/latina-equal-pay 💪🏽💪🏽🙌🏽🙌🏽👏🏽👏🏽

Our future as actors, performers, and writers are at risk… Our industry as a whole is at risk… We need to stand up for ourselves and fight for what is right and fair and deserved. It’s really scary to be out of work and not be able to provide for and support your families well-being, and to not be able to get have a job in a career that you’ve dedicated your life to… No one wants to strike! No one wants to be unemployed, without work… but we must take come together… I’m praying these negotiations will be worked out fairly across-the-board for everyone’s benefit, and that we all win! I stand in solidarity with my union @sagaftra and with the @wgastrikeunite @wgaeast @wgawest #WGA #SAG/AFTRA #actors #writers #performers #WeMatter #WeCount #fairness 👊🏽🙏🏽💪🏽

Me and my friends, my fellow actors are standing, walking and dancing, out loud for Justice for us actors, performers and writers!!! Our unions @sagaftra and @wgaunity @wgawest @wgaeast are fighting relentlessly to come to a fair agreement for ALL of us!! United we stand! Divided we fall! Our beautiful professions are at risk! Possibly not being able to  sustain a career anymore!  I like many of us  have trained since I was a child to be an actor and performer, I’ve  worked very hard to have a successful, lucrative career that could not only carry me and my family, but help others in need… The fact that we  may not be able to support and provide for our families is excruciatingly, scary and horrible for us! Actors performers, and writers count!  we are important and we should never be replaced by anyone, especially AI !! we are human beings, and we have a right to work and get compensated fairly! I pray we all continue to stand with each other, and we all come to an agreement sooner than later, so we can move forward, successfully and positively …🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽👊🏽👊🏽👊🏽💪🏽💪🏽💪🏽

Today was just spectacular!! The energy, the passion, the excitement and the solidarity… Absolutely exhilarating! What a gift to see all my beautiful Latino people show up today! We are fighting for our lives… Literally… For the ability to make our health insurance, to afford homes, to provide for our families, and to protect our beautiful profession, our creativity. All of these things are at risk during the strike. I pray these negotiations will come to an end  soon with a mutual feeling of fairness, goodness, and the ability to survive! For all of us! Come join us for a free and invaluable experience as we prepare for #LatinaEqualPayDay !! These last months we’ve taken a firm stance on fair and sustainable wages. And as Latinas, we still have to catch up on what that wage IS!!! DETAILS below, RSVP link in Bio.. Hope to see you hermanas there!! 
•
•
Join us on 9/30 for a day of power & community building as we prepare for #LatinaEqualPay Day! 
When & Where: Saturday, September 30 from 8:30 am -Noon @ LiUNA Local 300 | 2005 W Pico Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90006. Programming begins at 9:00am, come at 8:30am to enjoy breakfast & get your official campaign shirt for 2023!
Latina Equal Pay Day is on October 5, the day we observe the pay gap of 52 cents when looking at all Latinas with reported earnings, which is often even wider for immigrants, LGBTQIA+ Latinas and Afrolatinas. 
The Justice for Migrant Women, the Labor Council for Latin American Advancement and the Equal Pay Today Campaign are hosting a day of action on September 30 as we lead up to Latina Equal Pay Day. 
We will confront the systems that cause the pay gap and address how unions can help combat the wage gap and support Latinas in the workplace. 
We will also ensure community members have the information they need about their rights in the workplace and ongoing policy campaigns to strengthen workplace protections and close the wage gap.
RSVP link in bio: The event is free- share with your friends and family!

Latinas Unite! Turn up THIS Friday, September 29th at Warner Bros Studios- Gate 3, 4201 W. Olive Ave., Burbank from 10:00am to Noon. 

Congrats to our siblings @wgawest @wgaeast @uaw.union for the progress you have made to hold the line and advance the interests of your members. We are rooting you on! We also know there is more work to do.

Join this action in solidarity with working Latinas. From actors to writers, hotel workers, city workers, nurses, auto workers and more, we will unite with shared determination to push for better conditions for Latinas and all working people.

The action is organized by Latinas Acting Up, which was co-founded by my amigas and Latina leaders, SAG-AFTRA members and actresses @dianamariariva and @thereallisavidal. @mujerxsrising is proud to organize alongside you with our partners @lclaa @equalpay2dayorg @equalrightsadv @mamasconpoder @poderistas @thelatinxhouse @weallgrowlatina & @mana_national & many more great orgs & folks. Working Latinas, Latine community members & our allies will gather from across industries and sectors to demonstrate our collective power. #Trabajadoras #DemandMore #LatinaEqualPay #Pagame #1U

This #hispanicheritagemonth we are excited to be highlighting one of the pioneers in our talented, vibrant and inspirational Latino entertainment community @thereallisavidal 👏👏
Lisa is an award winning actress and is most recognizable for the multi-dimensional roles she’s played on television and in film for the past forty years, portraying characters that have reflected the diversity of the Latino community while also building it up. She recently starred in ABC romantic comedy-drama “The Baker and the Beauty.” Based on the highly successful Israeli scripted show, Vidal portrayed Mari Garcia, the hilarious and heartwarming matriarch of the family. She will next be seen in a wonderful arc on the hilarious and Emmy nominated series “Ms. Pat” on BET as well as the second season of the Gloria Calderón Kellett series “With Love” for Amazon. 
We are so honored and excited to dive into Lisa’s experience and have this opportunity to learn and gain wisdom from her. Thank you so much Lisa for giving back to the community and lifting others up! 
You will not want to miss this conversation so save the date, put it in your calendar and join us here on our Instagram this Monday at 12pm PST/3pm EST! Hosted by L.I.F.E. Co-founder @angeliqueivetterivera. 
If you’d like a question answered please email info@somoslife.org with the subject line “LIFE Pioneer Live with Lisa Vidal”. See you soon!

Today is #LatinaEqualPayDay!! it is the day that we observe the fact that working Latinas in the US with reported earnings in 2022(full time, part time, part year and seasonal workers) we’re paid just $.52 to the dollar. TODAY we shine a light on the fact that some working Latinas face even wider pay gaps, like working Latinas who were born outside of the US who are paid on average just $.46 to the dollar. TODAY we join forces to #DEMANDMORE Latinas should be paid every single cent that we earn! The full dollar for every hour worked, ITS LONG PAST TIME!! Go to www.LatinaEqualPay.Org for more information to take action TODAY thank you @lclaa @equalpay2dayorg @weallgrowlatina & @karla.and.co and to all of our partners throughout the US, let’s do this! This moment right here makes my heart burst! Thank you so much @poderistas for The honor of recognizing Latinas, acting up! This amazing, wonderful group of talented, powerful Latina actresses and performers came out of such a pure thought from Diana and I to get a few of us together to show unity and solidarity as Latinas in our  business and union. and look at the amazing thing that has grown to be what it is today! I am so proud of our incredible group of Latinas who joined in, showed up, and supported us in so many ways… I am forever, grateful, and honored to be a part of this.
